values:
I think I need to just accept that my birthday is cursed and learn to stop caring. I have had one good birthday that I can remember and the rest have ranged between mediocre and downright bad. My birthday always fails. Not even a paid trip to Vegas can save the curse that is my birthday. Birthday curse wins. The years before that when I tried to plan something for myself, it always ended up bleh. This year isn't going to be that promising either. Why? I'm spending it at a wedding where the bride doesn't even like me. Whoo hoo! So much fun.&nbsp;

And yet I have friends that are trying to salvage this for me. The topic comes up and what happens? I start crying at work. Why? Because I have no actual faith that it can be salvaged. The same thing will happen that always happens. I'll invite a bunch of friends and the majority of them won't come for one reason or another, so I'll be sad and disappointed. Though I guess sad and disappointed is better than sick or injured like my usual Halloweens. But still. By and large, my birthdays suck.&nbsp;

So whatever. I give up. I'm not even going to bother expecting my friends to make time for me and set myself for disappointment like every other year. It's not exciting anymore. It's depressing. A miserable birthday spent at an awkward wedding is just par for the course now.&nbsp;

I think the only time I ever update is to rant or something.&nbsp;

I'm at that&nbsp;SPAZZ point now of "omg it's almost con time and I'm not as finished with stuff as&nbsp;I'm supposed to be!". Gloves are an annoying thing to have to make... I made one and am not even happy with it so going to try to make the other look better.. in which case I'll need to remake the first. I have to&nbsp;tear out and recut half of my dress, which pisses me off. I still have to get the boas and barretts for my&nbsp;veil and hair clips, so those things haven't even been started yet, along with my bouquet. I have to do all this in two weeks,&nbsp;as well as hopefully have time to finish Trunks touchups and to make Hiei. /rantrant

And I'm still tired x.x Saw a midnight showing of Iron Man on thursday - much awesomeness - which was fine, but then the going back over to Kim's friday, saturday, sunday, and tuesday.. I'm&nbsp;so tired I can barely manage to work on anything. Oddly enough, I'm getting less work done at Kim's than&nbsp;usual. If I wasn't already taking the days off for Fanime I'd be so tempted to take a couple off just to grind out the costumes. But if I take one or two more off this month I won't get my paid day or my raise -.-;&nbsp;And I'm doing the midnight showing thing again tomorrow night for Speed Racer. But I think as long as I don't have to go out every day again afterward I'll be fine and can get more work done without wearing myself out and wasting time commuting.&nbsp;

I fear now for AX and Comiccon, because our game is supposed to be out in two months or so, which means likely overtime around then, when I'll be needing to grind costumes for CC... Hopefully not, but&nbsp;most likely.&nbsp;Just about every project goes into OT&nbsp;before submission. And now my break's over and I go back to the tedium. &nbsp;
